case_circumstances: Richmond PD officers responded to an open field area of the 100 block of W. Ohio Ave, to investigate a citizens report of a found deceased infant, rolled up in a blanket.  The infant was a new born white female.  It is unknown how long the infant was left in the field.  The infant's autopsy revealed no cause of death.  Richmond PD is looking for information locating a 61 year-old white female, by the name of Jeanie Ann Craft (aka Jeanie Manrigue, Jeanie Manrique, Jeanie Giovianni or Jeanie Sanders).  Ms. Craft's last known whereabouts is unknown.
fingerprints: Fingerprint information is currently not available
